---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Lithuania Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/lithuania/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Latvia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/latvia' },
  { title: 'Poland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/poland' },
  { title: 'Estonia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/estonia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'lithuaniaFit', header: 'Lithuania Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€280-400/mo', lithuaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€330-470/mo', lithuaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€260-370/mo', lithuaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€240-350/mo', lithuaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Lithuanian PSDF', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '6.98% income', lithuaniaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€260-400', annual: '€3,120-4,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€360-530', annual: '€4,320-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€480-720', annual: '€5,760-8,640' },
  { category: 'Lithuanian Public (PSDF)', monthly: '6.98% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Lithuanian Private Clinic', monthly: '€30-100', annual: '€360-1,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Lithuania 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Lithuania. Vilnius baroque, Baltic coast, affordable EU living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Lithuania"
  subheadline="Lithuania offers baroque Vilnius, Curonian Spit beaches, affordable living, and EU membership—the largest Baltic state with growing appeal for retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/lithuania-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Lithuania</h2>
  <p>
    Lithuania combines rich history, beautiful nature, and remarkable affordability. Vilnius Old Town is UNESCO-listed with stunning baroque architecture. The Curonian Spit offers unique sand dune landscapes. EU membership ensures European standards and easy regional travel.
  </p>

  <p>
    Vilnius provides capital-city culture with excellent healthcare access. Kaunas offers second-city charm with modernist architecture. Klaipėda delivers coastal living and gateway to Curonian Spit. Smaller towns provide extreme affordability and peaceful retirement.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good in Vilnius; improving nationally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Lithuanian; Russian less common; English in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,200-2,200/month; very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Baltic; cold winters, mild summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Highlight:</strong> Curonian Spit UNESCO World Heritage</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Lithuania's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Lithuania has public healthcare funded through PSDF (Compulsory Health Insurance Fund). Quality has improved significantly with EU membership. Vilnius has good hospitals including Santaros Klinikos, one of the largest medical centers in the Baltics.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is growing. Clinics like Northway, Kardiolita, and Affidea offer modern facilities with shorter waits. Many Lithuanians and expats use private care for faster service. Costs are very reasonable—consultations €30-60, much lower than Western Europe.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">English in Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      English is more common in Lithuania than other Baltic states, especially among younger professionals. Private clinics in Vilnius often have English-speaking staff. Public hospitals may have more language challenges. Having a translator or Lithuanian friend can help navigate public system.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Lithuania offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Financial Independence)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically €1,000+/month) and health insurance. Apply at Lithuanian embassy. Valid up to 2 years, renewable. Can lead to permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Lithuania has a startup/digital nomad-friendly environment. If you have remote work income, this provides residence pathway. Requires €3,000+/month income and health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with Migration Department after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Access to Lithuanian healthcare once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Lithuania:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Lithuanian system</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can access PSDF if contributing</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> For quality care and specialist access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Lithuania</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Lithuanian private healthcare is affordable enough to pay cash for routine needs. Keep international coverage for complex care, specialists, and potential evacuation if needed. Consider combining with local private clinic access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Lithuania, these providers offer good value:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Lithuania</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Baltic pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Lithuanian Private:</strong> Northway, Kardiolita for local care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that accept seniors for Lithuania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Lithuania are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €5,000+ deductible reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Cash routine care:</strong> Private consultations €30-60; easy cash payment</li>
    <li><strong>Baltic coverage:</strong> Plans covering all three Baltic states efficiently</li>
    <li><strong>PSDF access:</strong> If employed/self-employed, access public system</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American History Enthusiast, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Fascinated by Baltic history and Vilnius architecture.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa and comprehensive coverage. Uses Northway clinic for routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€350/month. Lives excellently in Vilnius Old Town on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Nature Lover, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, seeking EU with nature. Pension £1,800/month. Loves Curonian Spit.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for main coverage. Lives in Klaipėda with Spit access. UK coverage included.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€450/month. Peaceful coastal lifestyle on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Polish EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Warsaw to Vilnius. Polish pension €1,200/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for Lithuanian coverage. Add Allianz for Poland visits. Private locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Lithuanian public + Allianz (Lithuania excluded) ~€240/month. Great value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Lithuania different from the other Baltic states?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. Lithuania is largest and most populous. Lithuanian is unique (not related to Latvian/Estonian). Historically more Polish/Catholic influence vs. Nordic/Protestant in Estonia. Vilnius has baroque/Catholic architecture; Tallinn is medieval/Northern European. Each has distinct character.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is the Curonian Spit?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        A UNESCO World Heritage sand dune peninsula shared between Lithuania and Russia (Kaliningrad). Unique landscape with massive dunes, forests, and charming villages. Car ferry access from Klaipėda. Thomas Mann's summer home is there. One of Europe's most unusual natural wonders.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Lithuania really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very affordable. Comfortable life in Vilnius costs €1,500-2,000/month. Restaurant meals €8-15. Rent in center €500-800. Outside Vilnius even cheaper. Healthcare is affordable. Overall, 50-60% cheaper than Western Europe with good quality of life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Lithuanian hard to learn?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Lithuanian is one of Europe's oldest languages with complex grammar—challenging for English speakers. However, English is increasingly common, especially in Vilnius among younger people. You can manage with English in cities, though learning basics helps with daily life and integration.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Lithuania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Lithuanian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
